en_4494729_0	Colombo (News 1st): The supply of water to many areas in Moneragala was suspended until tomorrow (August 3) following reports of Grease and Oil contaminating the water in the Kumbukkan Oya.
en_4494729_1	Waste was released to the Kumbukkan Oya from the Albesia Power Plant of the Ceylon Electricity Board.
en_4494729_2	The National Water Supply and Drainage Board said, therefore, the supply of water to the Moneragala Town and surrounding areas was suspended.
en_4494729_3	The Disaster Management Centre said as a result around 50,000 families in Moneragala, Madulla and Okkampitiya will thus be affected and measures are underway to provide water using bowsers.
